race.comment: AVIATRESS (4) clearly looks the one to beat. She's been in fine form this campaign, winning the Village Stakes here three back, close up in her next two against the boys. She gave away 4kg to Disneck in the G3 Standish Handicap at Flemington last time and ran very well. Back to mare's grade here at set weights and drawn well, it looks a good scenario. WROTE TO ARATAKI (1) looks the blowout hope at odds. She resumes here with the peak figures to challenge. She's better over a touch further but has run some good races around this level and draws for every chance here. CIGAR FLICK (8) has been okay in two runs back in Sydney. She likes finding bad luck but has the turn of foot to challenge. A LITTLE DEEP (7) wasn't far away behind Hedged last time which ties in with AVIATRESS. She goes well fresh and has claims.
